<HEADLINE> 10 Tonnes of Drugs Seized in Turkey in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized over 10
tonnes of drugs in the operations against drug trafficking in the
whole Turkey this year.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Security General Directorate said a total of 2,928
operations were launched against drug smugglers between January 1
and December 16, 1998 in Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Drugs seized by the Turkish police in these operations include
5.348 tonnes of hashish, 3.766 tonnes of heroin, 604 kilograms of
cocaine, 123 kilograms of opium, among other things.
</P>
<P>
Police detained 5,172 Turkish people and 293 foreigners in
connection with the drug smugglings, and 15 drug smugglers were
killed in clashes with the police.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border areas of
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
