<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sweden Beats Russia to Take Baltika Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 20 (Xinhua) -- World champion Sweden took the
Baltika Cup on Sunday after beating Russia 5-3 helped by Christer
Olsson's twice scoring.
</P>
<P>
"We are satisfied with the results. We tried out several new
players for the world championships," Swedish coach Sune Bergman
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The tournament was the third in the European Hockey Tour.
Sweden won the first one in the Czech Republic three months ago.
Finland claimed the Karjala Cup in November. The last tournament
will be played in Sweden in February 1999.
</P>
<P>
Sweden now leads the overall standings with 13 points,
followed by Finland with 10, the Czech Republic eight, and Russia
five. 
</P>
</TEXT>
