<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway, Russia Win Relays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Norway's men and Russia's
women both scored World Cup cross country relay victories in
Davos, Switzerland, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Triple Olympic champion Bjoern Daehlie helped Norway's men to
take the 4x10km (4x6 mile) classic/freestyle race, the foursome
completing the course in 1 hour, 38 minutes, 48.2 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's men trailed just by .3 seconds, while Austria clocked
the third-fastest aggregate time of 1:39:27.1.
</P>
<P>
Russia's women, led by double Olympic gold medallist Olga
Danilova and triple Olympic champion Larissa Lazutina, clinched
the 4x5km (4x3 mile) relay in 54:32.1, a 47.6 seconds ahead of
runnerup Italy, the Olympic bronze medallist.
</P>
<P>
A second Russian team finished third, 51.8 adrift. 
</P>
</TEXT>
