<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Limo Wins Cross-country Challenge Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's Richard Limo
outsprinted two rivals to win the opening round of the
International Amateur Athletic Federation (IAAF) World Cross
Challenge series on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Limo, who won the silver medal in the junior race at the world
championships in March, beat Ethiopian Haylu Mekonen into second
place. Pre-race favourite Paul Koech of Kenya, who led for most
of the race, finished third.
</P>
<P>
Koech, silver medallist behind compatriot Paul Tergat at the
world championships, was in the lead until 250 meters from the
line when he was overtaken by Mekonen, who had finished third
behind Limo in the world championship junior race.
</P>
<P>
The seven-race series ends with the world championships in
Belfast on March 28.
</P>
<P>
The women's six-km race was dominated by Ethiopian Gete Wami,
who won in Brussels for the second successive year.
</P>
<P>
Wami, the 1996 world cross country champion, won comfortably
ahead of Finland's Annemarie Sandell and Ethiopian Ayelech
Worku. 
</P>
</TEXT>
