<HEADLINE> Cook Informs Iran of Halt to Strikes against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook on Sunday told his Iranian counterpart Kamal Kharrazi
the military strikes against Iraq have been ceased as wished by
Iran.
</P>
<P>
Cook informed Kharrazi of the decision of Britain and the
U.S. at a telephone conversation, the Islamic Republic News
Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi welcomed the stop of the strikes against Iraq, saying
the public opinion in the Muslim states is adamantly against these
operations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the present crisis will be solved
through diplomatic means and voiced Tehran's readiness to help
bring about a peaceful solution to the Iraqi crisis.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi made a phone call to Cook Friday night, calling for an
immediate stop of the U.S. and British air and missile strikes
against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, he also said the U.S.-British unilateral
strikes against the Iraqi nation had caused serious concern in the
Muslim world, and Iran, as the OIC chairman, demanded an immediate
halt to the attacks.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced Iran's protest against a stray missile
strike on Iran's southwestern port city of Khorramshahr in
Khuzestan province on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
