<HEADLINE> mee122021hke - Arafat Welcomes End of Attacks on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 20 (Xinhua) - Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Chairman Yasser Arafat Sunday welcomed end of a
four-day U.S.-British air strike campaign against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio quoted Arafat as saying that it is important
that the attacks are over.
</P>
<P>
The PNA called on the international community to use
diplomatic means to address the Iraqi dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian police Sunday intervened in several pro-Iraq
demonstrations on the West Bank. No clashes were reported.
Some journalists covering the protests were briefly detained.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Britain ended air strikes against Iraq after a
fourth day of attacks on Sunday morning, saying their forces had
inflicted "significant damage" on Iraq's military facilities.
</P>
</TEXT>
