<HEADLINE> Sierra Leone Rebels Capture Diamond City of Koidu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone rebels of the
Revolutionary United Front have captured the diamond city of
Koidu in the east of the country following fierce fightings with
the west African peace-keeping force, ECOMOG, since last
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Sunday quoted ECOMOG officers in capital
Freetown as saying that "we could have beaten the rebels back but
it would have resulted in the loss of many civilian lives. We
are giving the civilians a few days to leave the town, then we
will strike and crush the rebels."
</P>
<P>
The rebels launched their attacks on Koidu held by the
Nigerian-led ECOMOG troops and the fighting continued until early
Saturday when the ECOMOG troops supported by local Kamajor
traditional hunters pulled back to the outskirts of the town.
</P>
<P>
According to aid workers, thousands of civilians had fled
Koidu toward a northeast town of Makeni and more than 10,000
people have reached Makeni, about 150 kilometers away from Koidu.
</P>
<P>
Koidu used to be Sierra Leone's second biggest city with a
population of about one million until two years ago and the
population has now been reduced to some 100,000 because of the
insecurity after a coup in May 1997 and a ban on diamond mining
imposed by the government of Ahmed Tejan Kabbah.
</P>
<P>
The ECOMOG force restored elected President Kabbah to power in
March this year after ousting the junta which ruled the country
from May 1997 to February 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, the rebels of the Revolutionary United Front are
still fighting in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Liberian President Charles Taylor Sunday said
that Liberia has closed its borders with Sierra Leone, adding
that the measure was taken to prevent the Sierra Leone violence
from spilling over into Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone has repeatedly accused Liberia of supporting the
rebels loyal to the ousted military government in Sierra Leone.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
