<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 21:00 GMT, December 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein Sunday said the
Iraqi people have come out victorious despite four nights of
U.S. and British military strikes on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In a short speech read over Iraqi TV Sunday evening, Saddam
Hussein praised the Iraqi people for their steadfastness when
facing the U.S.-British air strikes. (BC-Saddam-Speech-Victory)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Some 10,000 Jordanians staged protest against the
U.S.-British air strikes on Iraq in Amman Sunday afternoon, and
called for lifting of the eight-year-old U.N. sanctions against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrators, waving flags and chanting slogans, condemned the
attacks on Iraq and called on the United Nations to lift what they
said unjust sanctions on Iraq imposed since the 1991 Gulf
war. (BC-Jordan-Iraq-Protest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq announced on Sunday that its anti-raids forces
shot down 21 out of a total of 81 missiles fired by the U.S. and
Britain during their fourth round of air strikes against Iraq on
Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency quoted a military communique issued by
the General Command of the Iraqi Armed Force as stating that
U.S.-UK missiles targeted the residential quarters, civil
institutions, government premises, hospitals, factories and
refineries in addition to military units. (BC-Iraq-Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's Cabinet on Sunday approved a list of
conditions that the Palestinians must fulfill before the
implementation of the peace agreement signed two months ago could
continue.
</P>
<P>
These conditions demand the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) halt the violence and incitement against Israel, reduce the
police forces and collect all illegal weapons.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the PNA must give up its demand for the release of
Palestinian political prisoners in Israeli jails and abandon all
unilateral statements on declaring statehood on May 4, 1999,
according to the conditions. (BC-Israel-Palestine-Conditions)
</P>
</TEXT>
