<HEADLINE> Kidnapped Boy Rescued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- A six-year-old boy kidnapped ten
days ago has been rescued by police in China's northwest Qinghai
Province and four migrant workers have been charged with the
abduction.
</P>
<P>
The boy is now back with his parents after more than 300
police scoured the area and the three adjacent provinces of Gansu,
Shaanxi and Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
The drama unfolded when Zhou Genlan, a private businessman
from the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, found his son Zhou
Jiang missing on December 2 and reported the case to the police
the next day.
</P>
<P>
The police discovered that the boy had been kidnapped by Hu
Guoqing and three other migrant workers from central Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
Three days later, on December 5, Zhou received a telephone
call from Hu, demanding a ransom of 170,000 yuan (about 21,000 US
dollars) for the boy.
</P>
<P>
While Zhou and his wife handed the money to the four kidnappers
in Leshan in southwest China's Sichuan Province, policemen who had
hidden nearby jumped out and arrested the gang, who were also
armed with three home-made handguns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
