<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
start its overhaul of the national sports development program
early next year following what officials has described as the
country's "worse performance" ever in an Asian sports contest.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines News Agency Monday quoted Executive Secretary
Ronaldo Zamora of the government as saying the new sports
development program will focus on schools as the primary venue
for developing international competitors.
</P>
<P>
"The result (in the Asian Games) is that we end up at the
bottom in international competition. This is the worst
performance we ever had in any international competition in
Asia," Zamora said
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, Philippine President Joseph Estrada expressed
disappointment over the country's sports development program
following the Philippines' dismal performance in the 13th Asian
Games in Bangkok, Thailand, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
He described the Philippine contingents' performances as "very
disappointing".
</P>
<P>
The Philippines earned only one gold medal from billiards in
the 13th Asian Games. 
</P>
