<HEADLINE> Bank of China Gives State Firms Huge Loan Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) today
sealed a cooperative agreement with China North Industrials
Corporation, promising to grant it a credit line of up to four
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A leader in foreign-exchange banking and the most profitable
bank in the nation, the BOC has inked similar cooperative
agreements with dozens of large enterprises this year, and the
credit line it has extended to these clients already exceed 50
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the BOC is expected to fund the
company with loans in domestic currency and foreign exchanges,
bills of acceptance, discount promissory notes, and
guarantees. The BOC also will provide the company with all-round
financial services including settlements, consultation, securities
underwriting, and funds management.
</P>
<P>
Besides the foreign trade of special products, machinery and
electronic products, China North Industrials Corporation is also
involved in international economic cooperation, projects
contracting, and industrial investment. One of the nation's
largest state enterprises, with assets of more than 24 billion
yuan, the company has engaged in foreign trade worth more than 25
billion U.S. dollars to date. 
