<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Praises Cambodian King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
spoke highly today of Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk's important
role in safeguarding political stability and promoting national
reconciliation in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Whenever the Cambodian situation came to a critical point,
Sihanouk always placed the priority on the interests of his
country and his people, and has demonstrated patriotism and superb
political acumen, said Jiang during his meeting with Sihanouk and
Cambodian Queen Norodom Monineath in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Sihanouk said that the Chinese government and the
Chinese people have given the Cambodian people great help and
support over a long period of time, which will never be forgotten.
</P>
<P>
He added that positive progress has been made in the Cambodian
situation recently, and that the country was grateful for China's
understanding and help in resolving some domestic problems.
</P>
<P>
Jiang described Sihanouk as China's old friend and the
founder of the Sino-Cambodian friendship, commenting that the
Chinese government and people highly valued Sihanouk's
contributions to that ongoing relationship.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed his thanks for Sihanouk's donation to
China of 20,000 US dollars this summer when China was affected by
severe floods.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk said that he will continue to make contributions to
the friendship between Cambodia and China.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk arrived in Beijing last month for a routine health
check. 
</P>
