<DOCNO> XIE19981221.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Consumer Price Indices for November 1998 Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's consumer price
inflation, as indicated by the year-on-year rate of change in the
composite Consumer Price Index (CPI), registered a decline of 0.7
percent in November, compared with a small increase of 0.1 percent
in October.
</P>
<P>
According to the CPI figures for November 1998 released Monday
by the Census and Statistics Department, analyzed by sub-index and
on a year-on-year comparison, the CPI(A), CPI(B) and Hang Seng CPI
fell by 0.9 percent, 0.9 percent and 0.2 percent respectively in
November.
</P>
<P>
The corresponding rates of change in October were -0.1 percent,
virtually nil and +0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
A Government Secretariat spokesman noted that the last time
that the overall consumer price inflation turned negative was back
in 1975.
</P>
<P>
This time, it reflected, to a large extent, the slack overall
economic conditions and the continuing process of cost and price
adjustment upon the impact of the regional financial turmoil, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Yet also contributing to the distinct easing in inflation were
the freezing in government fees and charges and in a number of
public utility charges, as well as the one-off rates rebate by
the government effective in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that the further easing in consumer prices
helped to contain the cost of living at a time when economic
conditions were more difficult.
</P>
<P>
Also, reduced costs, being part and parcel of the adjustment
process, helped to moderate the cost of doing business.
</P>
<P>
Compared with October 1998, the composite CPI for November
decreased by 0.6 percent. The corresponding decreases in the
CPI(A), CPI(B) and Hang Seng CPI were 0.8 percent, 0.8 percent and
0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
For the first 11 months of 1998, the increase in the composite
CPI averaged 3.2 percent over the same period in 1997. The
corresponding increases in the CPI(A), CPI(B) and Hang Seng CPI
were 3.0 percent, 3.2 percent and 3.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
