-- At least 21 people were killed and 27 wounded in renewed
fighting in the town of Sakow in southern Somalia, traditional
elders and the local press reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
-- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni said Sunday that he
skipped the Organization of African Unity talks in Ouagadougou
because the agenda was too broad to have a good chance of
arriving at a plausible solution.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard:
</P>
<P>
-- For the last six months, Kenya's public debt has increased
to 483 billion Shillings (around eight billion U.S. Dollars)
accounting for 68 percent of it gross domestic products (GDP),
according to the latest monthly review of the Central Bank of
Kenya. 
</P>
