<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Publicizes Tardy Tax-Payers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 21 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
provincial taxation bureau recently made public a list of 27
enterprises which have delayed paying their taxes in order to help
ensure timely tax payment.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth time the bureau made public the names of
the delinquent tax-payers, bringing the total number named to 127.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that since the first publication, many late
tax-payers have taken active steps to make payments, and some
cities have taken compulsory measures, including auctioning off
and distraining late tax-payers' properties, to force
compliance with tax law.
</P>
<P>
According to a bureau announcement, all late tax-payers
must pay their due taxes by the end of this year or face
severe penalties.
</P>
<P>
A bureau official said that measures will be taken to
ensure that over 30 percent of those delinquent pay
their taxes in full within this year. 
