<HEADLINE> Hebei Province to Increase Water-Saving Irrigation Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 21 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province will have an additional 667,000 hectares of water-saving
irrigation land by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official said that Hebei is one of the
most water-deprived provinces in the country, and has made great
efforts to improve its irrigation capabilities in recent years.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, Hebei is expected to have 2.31 million
hectares of water-saving irrigation land, which will save 2.2
billion cubic meters of water and increase Hebei's grain output by
1.5 billion kilograms annually.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has developed irrigation techniques with different
focuses for plains and mountainous areas, and is coordinating
water-saving irrigation with dry-land agriculture. 
</P>
