<HEADLINE> Share Prices Down Slightly on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower on
Singapore Stock Market Monday after the country's Trade
Development Board (TDB) released economic data showing that
Singapore's external trade slipped further in November.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shed 8.23 points to end
at 1,397.73 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover decreased to 120.55 million units worth
254.16 million Singapore dollars (154.11 million U.S. dollars).
Losers edged out gainers by 84 to 67 with 168 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land was the most active stock of the day with a turnover
of 7.67 million units. KepLand was the second most heavily traded
stock with a volume of 5.69 million units done. SingTel was next
with 4.52 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F led the ascent of the day rising by 50 cents to close at
14.50 Singapore dollars. OUB F was up 25 cents to finish at 7.20
Singapore dollars. UOB F gained 20 cents to end at 11.20 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
with a decline of 50 cents to 25.00 Singapore dollars. SIA F was
next shedding 40 cents to close at 12.60 Singapore dollars.
RothmansI sank 30 cents to end at 10.00 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that the stock market opened firmer in morning
session in early holiday-thinned trading as players reacted with
indifference to U.S. House votes to impeach President Bill
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
However, prices later eased back slightly after the TDB's
statistics revealed that Singapore's exports contracted by 7.3
percent in November compared to the same period in 1997, dealers
added.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also said the decline in Tokyo bourse also contributed
to the decline.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the market logically underwent a winding-down
process before a year-end.
</P>
<P>
They said the slowing down of activity for most of last week
and the largely quiet sessions pointed to a holiday mood and an
absence of many players because of the festive season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
