<HEADLINE> Thai Opposition Targets 3 Ministers in Censure Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Thai opposition parties are
targeting three key ministers in their planned confidence debate
with the motion to be submitted to Parliament next month.
</P>
<P>
They are Interior Minister Sanan Kachornprasart, Finance
Minister Tarrin Nimmanhaeminda and Transport and Communications
Minister Suthep Thueksuban, opposition sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Although the opposition failed in its impeachment attempt
against some key ministers earlier this month, it would go ahead
with the censure bid in a separate motion, New Aspiration Party
spokesman Suraporn Danaitangtrakoon said.
</P>
<P>
The opposition is hopeful that the censure motion would be
submitted to Parliament by January 10.
</P>
<P>
The opposition had previously submitted a motion seeking to
impeach Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai and Tarrin for issuing
letters of intent to obtain the bailout package from the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) without parliamentary approval.
</P>
<P>
Suraporn said he believed that the validity of the impeachment
motion would be determined before the censure move.
</P>
<P>
The Counter Corruption Commission decided last weekend to pass
the impeachment motion to the Constitutional Court to rule on its
validity. The technical hitch has unexpectedly delayed the
opposition's move to get the motion debated in Parliament.
</P>
<P>
Suraporn told reporters that the no-confidence motion would
seek to bring to light "the corrupt practices" of some ministers
in the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman declined to identify the ministers to be
targeted in the debate.
</P>
<P>
Opposition sources said, however, that Sanan, Tarrin and Suthep
were the prime targets followed by ministers of the Prime Minister
Office Supatra Masdit and Jurin Laksanavisit.
</P>
<P>
The opposition would push for a two-day debate on the motion.
One full day would be devoted to debating the work of Sanan, the
sources said. 
</P>
