<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Slightly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar was
almost stagnate Monday, ending steady in soft, directionless
trade.
</P>
<P>
After trading in a tight range between 61.88 U.S. cents and
62.05 U.S. cents, the local currency finished at 62.01 U.S. cents
from 62.00 U.S. cents late last Friday.
</P>
<P>
A foreign exchange dealer from Bankers Trust said that "the
market, corporations and investors alike, has realized it is
Christmas week so they just come in, do what they have to do and
leave it alone for the rest of the day".
</P>
<P>
The factors playing on either side of the Australian dollar are
weak commodity prices and strength in the Japanese yen against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the local session the Australian dollar was
trading at 71.20 Japanese yen from 71.97 yen last Friday and
1.0282 German marks from 1.0310 marks. 
</P>
