<HEADLINE> Philippines Prepared for Terrorist Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine army and police
said Monday that they have been prepared for possible terrorist
attacks by the Mindanao-based extremist rebel group Abu Sayyaf.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency quoted National Police Chief
Director General Roberto Lastimoso and Army Chief of Staff Joselin
Nazareno as saying that they are ready for possible acts of
terrorism by the Abu Sayyaf to avenge the death of its leader
Abdurajak Abubakar Janjalani last week.
</P>
<P>
Lastimoso and Nazareno also said the terrorist group is not
capable of actually disrupting peace and order in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
"There is the possibility that the remnants, sympathizers or
even friends of the Abu Sayyaf will try to get even by conducting
some terroristic act to embarrass the government," Lastimoso said.
</P>
<P>
Janjalani, the most wanted criminal in the Philippines, was
killed in an encounter with government troops in Basilan,
Mindanao, last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The extremist rebel group has conducted a series of criminal
activities in the past few years, including the killing of 54
civilians in the town of Ipil, the Southern Philippines, in April
1995.
</P>
<P>
Nazareno said the military is keeping tabs on "all forces" that
intend to conduct terrorist activities, particularly on embassies.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
