<DOCNO> XIE19981221.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Only Deaf Ballet Dancer to Perform in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The only hearing-impaired
ballet dancer in the world, Kang Jim Hee of the Republic of Korea,
will make her first appearance in China next January.
</P>
<P>
Invited by the Chinese Dancers Association, the Cho Seung Mi
Dance Company in which Kang performs, will stage the ballet
"Samson and Delilah" on January 2-3, with Kang dancing the role of
Delilah.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six-year-old Kim was born deaf, and even with the
assistance of an audiophone can barely hear the siren
of a train. However, with her special talent and through hard
work, she has been able to realize considerable achievements.
</P>
<P>
In 1992 she won a national dance competition for university
students; in 1993 she placed second at an international
ballet competition in Japan, and the same year took part in
the Moscow international ballet competition where she was awarded
a prize.
</P>
<P>
For her achievements, President Kim Young-Sam and President Kim
Dae-Jung recognized her with special presidential awards in 1995
and 1998 as a tribute to her courage in overcoming disability.
</P>
<P>
Many people wonder how Kang manages to follow the rhythm and
keep in step with her partners. Her teacher Cho simply attributes
Kang's virtuosity to her talent and constant practice. The Chinese
dancer who will play the role of Samson said it is unbelievable
that Kang has made herself such a wonderful dancer when their
feelings can only be exchanged through the sense of touch.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
