<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian Drug Enforcement
Commission (DEC) has arrested two people for trafficking drugs
worth 78.4 million Kwacha (about 32,660 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Zambia's daily newspaper, the Post, Monday quoted DEC
spokesman Mukutulu Sinyani as saying in a statement that
41-year-old Tanzanian Erisaria Masawe was found with two carton
boxes, each containing ten bundles of fresh khat (mirra) wrapped
in banana leaves in Kapiri Mposhi, about 200 kilometers north of
Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
The man was traveling by bus from Muyombe in Northern Province
to Lusaka. His contraband weighing 15.17 kilograms has an
estimated street value of 63.7 million Kwacha (some 26,540
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the same bus, a 33-year-old woman identified as Gertrude
Banda, who is living in Lusaka, was found with two large
traveling bags and some polythene bags full of carefully
concealed marijuana weighing 26.737 kilograms with a street value
of 14.7 million Kwacha (some 6,120 Dollars). 
