<HEADLINE> China Using More Foreign Loans for Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- China has used 4.5 billion
U.S. dollars worth of foreign loans to construct 9,000 kilometers
of highways, according to a report in the "China Reform News."
</P>
<P>
The loans were provided by such international financial
organizations as the World Bank and the Asian Development Bank and
by foreign governments. The money has been used to finance highway
construction in all of the country's 24 provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities, the newspaper quoted an official with
the Ministry of Communications as saying.
</P>
<P>
The official said the central Chinese government encourages
more domestic and overseas economic organizations to invest in
highway construction.
</P>
<P>
Companies engaged in developing and maintaining highways are
permitted to raise funds by way issuing shares or corporate bonds
in accordance with relevant laws and regulations, he added.
</P>
<P>
The building of highways through the formation of joint
ventures and cooperative companies is quite popular in eastern
coastal areas and some economically developed regions in the
country. South China's Guangdong Province, for instance, has
obtained 12 percent of its total investment for highway
construction from overseas investors, and more than a half its
funds for expressway construction from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The official disclosed that China will take steps to increase
the use of foreign capital in highway construction in the future,
especially by introducing more foreign funds for this purpose into
central and western areas of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
