<HEADLINE> China Increasing Supervision Of Individual Incomes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- China will increase
supervision of individual incomes for more stable and rapid growth
in taxes, according to today's overseas edition of People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
The paper says that tax work will focus on individual incomes
of foreigners and incomes from overseas, dividends of
stock-issuing companies and fund-managing companies, incomes of
individuals from house rents, and income from special consumer
sectors like dance halls, karaoke rooms, and beauty saloons.
</P>
<P>
Individual income taxes had rapid growth from January to
November, with 30.2 billion yuan (3.64 billion U.S. dollars) in
taxes assessed, an increase of 29.8 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
To reach its goal of 100 billion yuan this year, the State
Administration of Taxation recently asked tax departments to be
stricter. 
</P>
