<HEADLINE> Hackl Wins Luge World Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 BONN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Georg Hackl of Germany,
three-time Olympic champion, won the luge World Cup race and took
the lead in overall luge World Cup standings in Winterberg,
Germany on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
32-year-old Hackl clocked a winning aggregate time of one
minute, 50.486 seconds. The victory gave Hackl 309 points after
four of seven events.
</P>
<P>
 Markus Prock of Austria was second in 1:50.578 and is second
ranked with 290.
</P>
<P>
 Adam Heidt of the United States came third in 1:50.578.
</P>
<P>
 Armin Zoeggeler of Italy, 11th in the event, fell from first
to third with 287.
</P>
<P>
 The World Cup tour resumes in Oberhof, Germany on January
16 after the holiday break. 
</P>
