<HEADLINE> Dalian, Singapore Join Hands to Reconstruct Dalian Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, December 21 (Xinhua) --The Dalian Port Authority of
northeast China's Liaoning Province and PSA Co. Ltd. of Singapore
have signed a contract to jointly rebuild the eastern part of the
Dalian Port.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time the two partners have cooperated,
having earlier collaborated in the construction of a container
berth near Dayao Bay in Dalian.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, Dalian Marine Ltd., the new company,
will involve a total investment of 2.8 million U.S. dollars to be
shared equally by the two partners.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that reconstruction of the eastern part of
the port of Dalian will focus on moving existing cargo transport
berths out of this section and moving them to newly expanded port
areas such as Dayao Bay. The effort also aims to turn the eastern
part into a tourism, passenger transport, and commerce and trade
area.
</P>
<P>
The new company will soon work out a detailed plan for
developing the eastern part in accordance with Dalian's urban
development blueprint, and organize investment promotion
according to international standard practices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
