<HEADLINE> U.S. And European Furniture Competing In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 21 (Xinhua) -- A recent study in Shanghai
has found that the city will become a battleground for 400
furniture businesses from the U.S. and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Furniture companies from the U.S., Britain, Italy, Germany,
France, Australia and other western countries have expressed a
desire to compete in Shanghai's furniture market.
</P>
<P>
Since the early '90s, furniture sales in Shanghai have grown at
least 20 percent annually, far exceeding the average of 8 percent
nationally, and annual international furniture fairs for the past
two years have done a billion yuan (120 million U.S. dollars) in
business each.
</P>
<P>
Italy took the lead in entering Shanghai's furniture market and
the products of more than 100 Italian furniture companies can be
found in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
In September, a team from 7 Western furniture enterprises made
a special trip to the Shanghai Business Center and signed up for
4,000 sq.m. of space for an exhibition.
</P>
<P>
A Shanghai furniture group plans to open an 800 sq.m. hall by
next February to display the products of 50 leading U.S. furniture
businesses. The group also plans to build a 12,000 sq.m. shopping
mall to sell U.S. furniture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
