<HEADLINE> Corinthians Draws with Cruzeiro again in Soccer Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Corinthians drew with
Cruzeiro 1-1 in the second leg of the three-match Brazilian
championship final on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Under the intricacies of the championship, Corinthians need
only to draw Wednesday's third leg, when they will again have
home advantage, to win the title for the second time. Last week's
first leg had ended in a 2-2 draw.
</P>
<P>
Marcelinho Carioca of Corinthians scored a goal early in the
second half with his 18th goal of the championship.
</P>
<P>
But Cruzeiro levelled the score 10 minutes later through
striker Marcelo Ramos.
</P>
<P>
Cruzeiro dominated the later stages but the Corinthians
defence was excellently marshalled by Carlos Gamarra.
</P>
<P>
The tie is decided on points, then on goal difference and
finally first stage records. Corinthians need only a draw on
Wednesday as they won the first stage, which also gives them home
advantage for the decisive match. 
