<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Launch Giant Balloon to Monitor Ozone Layer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 21 (Xinhua) -- China is preparing to launch
a 30,000-cubic meter weather balloon on January 1, 1999 to monitor
the atmospheric ozone layer across the country over the next three
to five years.
</P>
<P>
According to officials, it will be the world's first balloon
sent to a 30,000-meter altitude to monitor the ozone layer.
</P>
<P>
China will also launch a second smaller balloon, of some
1,000-cubic meters, next February for the same purpose.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring program has been initiated by the Institute of
Atmospheric Physics attached to the Chinese Academy of Sciences in
partnership with a foreign refrigerant producer.
</P>
<P>
Reports indicate that damage to the ozone layer is one of the
world's three major environmental problems.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to help protect the vital ozone layer, China has now
decided to gradually stop the production of refrigerant and
foaming agents containing carbon fluorine chlorine which destroys
ozone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
