<HEADLINE> Record Heroin Confiscated in Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police confiscated
207.65 kilograms of heroin in south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region last month.
</P>
<P>
Police say that it was the largest haul of heroin in Guangxi
since founding of new China in 1949, and the third largest in the
country this year.
</P>
<P>
On November 24, police from the Bose City Public Security
Bureau examined a cargo truck at the Bailin Bridge and discovered
384 packages of heroin.
</P>
<P>
The alleged two male traffickers, named as Li Changxing and
Duan Changxiang respectively, are from Longlin County and Shixun
County of southwest China's Yunnan Province and have been detained
while investigations continue. 
