<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wild Ginkgo Trees Found in China's Guizhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 6,300 wild ginkgo
trees were discovered recently in Wuchuan Gelao Autonomous County
in southwest China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
Xiang Yinghai, president of the Guizhou Provincial Academy of
Sciences, said that wild ginkgo trees almost vanished from the
earth during the Fourth Ice Age, and now they are found only in
remote mountainous regions such as Wuchuan.
</P>
<P>
The ginkgo trees in Wuchuan are an important source of income
for local farmers since each tree may bring them as much as
several thousand yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
