<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arsenal Claims First Victory in League Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Arsenal
claimed their first victory in six Premier League matches by
beating Leeds United 3-1 at Highbury on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The win kept Arsenal within four points of league leaders
Chelsea, which beat Tottenham Hotspur 2-0 on Saturday to go top
for the first time in nine years.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal went ahead against the run of play when Dennis
Bergkamp latched on to a precise 40 meter pass by Emmanuel Petit
and chipped into the net in the 28th minute.
</P>
<P>
They made it 2-0 early in the second half with a powerful shot
by Patrick Vieira following more good work by Petit, returning
from injury for his first game since November 21.
</P>
<P>
Leeds reduced the deficit in the 66th minute when Jimmy Floyd
Hasselbaink drove in a 20 meter shot of stunning ferocity.
</P>
<P>
But Arsenal, who blew a 2-0 lead last week when they lost 3-2
to Aston Villa, finished the stronger. They missed several good
chances before Petit finished off a sweeping move with a first
time shot eight minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
The game ended on a sour note for Arsenal as French substitute
Gilles Grimandi was sent off for butting Leeds youngster Alan
Smith in the 86th minute.
</P>
<P>
The result lifted Arsenal one place to sixth, four points
behind leaders Chelsea and Aston Villa, who play Charlton
Athletic on Monday. Leeds remain fifth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981221.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miriona Moeva Swims 85,617.5 Meters in 24 Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sofia, December 20 (Xinhua) - Bulgarian Miriona Moeva will be
included in the Guinness Book of Records as the woman who swam
the longest distance in a 25-meter pool in 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
She swam 85,617.5 meters without leaving the pool from 6pm on
Saturday to 6pm on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Miriona accomplished a feat. I don't know if I can do the
same. I will inform the organizers of swimming marathons at sea
of her achievement because I'm sure she will represent Bulgaria
around the world just as well as I can," marathon swimmer Peter
Stoichev, who swam alongside Moeva most of the time, told BTA.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian Swimming Federation received a letter from the
Guinness Book publishers, saying that so far records had been set
under non-standardized conditions and swimming marathon
achievements would have to be recorded from scratch.
</P>
<P>
"We met the Guinness requirements for refereeing and pool
size, therefore Moeva's achievement will be registered as a
record. The papers will be sent on Monday," the Federation's
Stefan Zlatarov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
