<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine Tourism Authority and Overseas Workers
Welfare Administration Sunday rolled out the carpet for returning
overseas Filipino workers at the Ninoy Aquino International
Airport.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Daily Inquirer:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada said Sunday that he was
confident Southeast Asia had become a safer and better place to
live in after the region's leaders vowed to join hands in
attacking the Asian economic contagion and poverty and criminality
in the area.
</P>
<P>
Today:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada Sunday expressed
disappointment over the poor performance of the Philippine team in
the 13th Asian Games in Bangkok, and some sports officials may
lose their jobs because of it.  
</P>
