<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian:
</P>
<P>
-- The Howard government's decision to sneak in regulations
over the Christmas/New Year period allowing small firms to sack
new staff without fear of legal reprisal has backfired, with the
Senate now certain to overturn the move.
</P>
<P>
The Age:
</P>
<P>
-- The threat of further military strikes hung over Iraq Sunday
night as the United States and Britain declared an end to the
campaign in which more bombs exploded than during the 1991 Gulf
War.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- The Business Coalition for Tax Reform may recommend the
Howard government consider a move towards an expenditure-based
system as part of a radical overhaul of Australia's corporate
taxes. 
