<DOCNO> XIE19981221.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Star Anderson Faces Prison for Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Greg Anderson, a NBA star
in the Hawks team, faces a maximum of 40 years in prison for
participating in a cocaine deal.
</P>
<P>
He blamed bad judgement and a poor choice of friends for his
fate. The NBA veteran believed he would probably serve three to
four years in prison whith no chance for parole.
</P>
<P>
"They caught me red-handed," said Anderson, who has spent 10
years in the NBA. He was a first-round draft pick by the San
Antonio Spurs in 1987, and played for Milwaukee, Denver, Detroit
and Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
"I could have said, 'No,' I could have stopped this. But I
didn't. I'm not in a state of thinking, 'Why did this happen?' I
should have been saying tht before it happened. I should have
said a lot of things before it happened."
</P>
<P>
Anderson and three others pleaded guilty on October 20 to
possession of cocaine with intent to distribute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
